verbs.description: finedraw (third-person singular simple present finedraws, present participle finedrawing, simple past finedrew, past participle finedrawn)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To sew up so finely that the seam is not visible; to renter.
examples: and when one of larger dimensions was required, several of these were sewn finedrawn together with such care that no seams were discernible.
